me.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024_lisanandy_oasis_getty_2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024_lisanandy_oasis_getty_2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024_lisanandy_oasis_getty_2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024_lisanandy_oasis_getty_2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-industry-responds-to-lisa-nandy-mp-being-named-secretary-of-state-for-culture-media-and-sport-3772606">英国文化大臣</a>丽莎·南迪在她对英国音乐界的首次讲话中谴责了英国绿洲团圆巡演门票的动态定价。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-industry-responds-to-lisa-nandy-mp-being-named-secretary-of-state-for-culture-media-and-sport-3772606">音乐界对 Lisa Nandy MP 被任命为文化、媒体和体育国务秘书做出回应</a></strong></li></ul><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-ticket-sales-culture-secretary-lisa-nandy-calls-for-review-into-dynamic-pricing-and-secondary-ticket-sites-3789694">9月份，绿洲乐队备受期待的重聚巡演门票在英国和爱尔兰发售后，这位议员首次呼吁对“动态定价”和二级门票网站进行审查</a>。一些粉丝失望地 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-fans-react-to-ticketmasters-dynamic-pricing-3789361">发现，由于 Ticketmaster 在访问门票页面时采用动态定价政策，价格大幅上涨</a>。</p><p>该票务平台于 2022 年推出的“峰时定价”计划，根据需求提高门票价格。 Ticketmaster 此前曾在其网站上澄清，门票是“市场定价”的，并且“可能根据需求随时增加或减少”。这类似于机票和酒店房间的销售方式。”</p><p>在遭到粉丝的强烈反对后，绿洲公司<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-reunion-tour-band-say-they-at-no-time-had-any-awareness-that-dynamic-pricing-was-going-to-be-used-3790679">发表了一份声明</a>，其中写道：“绿洲公司将票务和定价的决定完全交给他们的促销员和管理层，并且从未意识到将使用动态定价。” </p><figure id="attachment_3801694" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3801694" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3801694" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/oasis-liam-noel-gallagher@2000x1270.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/oasis-liam-noel-gallagher@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/oasis-liam-noel-gallagher@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/oasis-liam-noel-gallagher@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/oasis-liam-noel-gallagher@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/oasis-liam-noel-gallagher@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/oasis-liam-noel-gallagher@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3801694" class="wp-caption-text">绿洲乐队的利亚姆和诺埃尔·加拉格尔。图片来源：Gareth Davies/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-confirm-dynamic-pricing-will-not-be-applied-to-north-american-reunion-tour-dates-3798327">乐队后来证实，动态定价结构不会应用于</a>他们的<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-announce-2025-reunion-tour-dates-in-north-america-and-mexico-buy-tickets-3798246">北美重聚巡演日期</a>。</p><p>周五（10 月 11 日），南迪在曼彻斯特音乐行业会议暨音乐节<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/aitch-announced-as-keynote-speaker-at-manchesters-beyond-the-music-festival-3794809">Beyond The Music</a>上发表讲话时，再次谴责了这一政策，并承诺解决现场音乐的“价格透明度”问题。</p><p> “我们已经宣布将于今年秋天启动一项咨询，”她在首次向音乐行业发表讲话时说道。 “对我们来说，这不是我们是否干预的问题，而是我们如何干预的问题。</p><p> “特别是，磋商将关注转售问题，在许多情况下，转售问题导致价格超出大多数人的承受能力。这种情况已经持续太久了。我们的承诺是解决这个问题。这不是是否的问题，而是如何的问题。”</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-partner-with-twickets-for-reunion-tour-3788427">Oasis 此前宣布与转售平台 Twickets 建立合作伙伴关系</a>，粉丝可以以不超过面值（加上预订费）的价格购买不需要的门票。</p><p>南迪接着特别强调了绿洲乐队的问题，以及粉丝排长队买票却发现自己无力承担新涨价的问题，他说：“我们不想看到这样的事情重演，所以我们我们正在研究如何提高透明度并防止这种情况发生。”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> “创建一个可以培养人才的生态系统，从优质音乐教育到磨练技能的基层场所，以及与你并肩同行的政府，创造一个创造机会的环境”</p><p>文化部长<a href="https://twitter.com/lisanandy?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@lisanandy</a>今天在<a href="https://twitter.com/gobeyondmcr?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@gobeyondmcr</a>上发言<a href="https://t.co/qMs4Zfyipy">pic.twitter.com/qMs4Zfyipy</a></p><p> — 文化、媒体和体育部 (@DCMS) <a href="https://twitter.com/DCMS/status/1844784179231215623?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2024 年 10 月 11 日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>在英国和爱尔兰的销售争议之后， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-reunion-tour-hundreds-complain-to-asa-over-surge-ticket-pricing-3789875">该问题被提交给广告标准局</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-european-commission-reportedly-investigating-dynamic-pricing-amid-oasis-tickets-controversy-3790240">欧盟委员会</a>，并单独呼吁<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-ticket-sales-culture-secretary-lisa-nandy-calls-for-review-into-dynamic-pricing-and-secondary-ticket-sites-3789694">英国政府进行调查</a>。</p><p>专家还建议，不警告 Oasis 粉丝动态定价<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/not-warning-oasis-fans-of-dynamic-pricing-may-be-law-breach-experts-say-3789896">可能违反消费者法</a>。</p><p>南迪还利用这次演讲解决了基层音乐场所面临的挑战，称政府“正在研究如何通过社区购买权改革，使社区拥有的社区建筑重新投入使用。”</p><p>近年来，随着音乐场馆信托基金#OwnOurVenues 计划的成功，社区所有权的话题日益盛行。该计划于<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-launch-scheme-to-purchase-uks-grassroots-music-venues-3229623" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2022 年</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-launch-scheme-to-purchase-uks-grassroots-music-venues-3229623">5 月首次公布</a>，一年后宣布取得成功， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/own-our-venues-campaign-succeeds-in-securing-first-funding-for-mvt-to-start-buying-uk-grassroots-gig-spaces-3424496">该慈善机构通过一系列捐赠和投资筹集了 230 万英镑</a>。</p><p>它被称为“国家信托，但针对场馆”，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-backs-music-venue-trusts-own-our-venues-campaign-3316937">得到了 Ed Sheeran 等人的支持</a>，场馆与音乐场馆地产 (MVP) 签署了一份“文化租赁”，保证只要它们作为草根空间运营为当地社区提供现场音乐，他们可以享受使用该建筑的乐趣。</p><p>到目前为止，三个场馆已受到该计划的保护。去年<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-buys-first-venue-under-national-trust-of-venues-public-ownership-scheme-3509198">10 月，阿瑟顿 (Atherton) 的 The Snug 成为第一个受到该计划拯救和保护的场所</a>， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-ferret-in-preston-saved-by-mvts-own-our-venues-scheme-3755247">随后是 5 月的普雷斯顿 (Preston) 的 The Ferret</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/swanseas-the-bunkhouse-saved-by-music-venue-trusts-ownourvenues-scheme-3797869">9 月的斯旺西 (Swansea) 草根音乐场所 The Bunkhouse</a> 。 </p><figure id="attachment_3797879" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3797879" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3797879" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Fontaines-D.C.-perform-at-The-Bunkhouse.-CREDIT_-Press.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Fontaines-D.C.-perform-at-The-Bunkhouse.-CREDIT_-Press.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Fontaines-D.C.-perform-at-The-Bunkhouse.-CREDIT_-Press-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Fontaines-D.C.-perform-at-The-Bunkhouse.-CREDIT_-Press-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Fontaines-D.C.-perform-at-The-Bunkhouse.-CREDIT_-Press-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Fontaines-D.C.-perform-at-The-Bunkhouse.-CREDIT_-Press-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Fontaines-D.C.-perform-at-The-Bunkhouse.-CREDIT_-Press-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3797879" class="wp-caption-text"> Fontaines DC 在 The Bunkhouse 表演。图片来源：新闻界</figcaption></figure><p>此举正值英国小型音乐场所面临危机之际。今年早些时候，音乐场馆信托基金 (Music Venue Trust) 发布了<a href="https://www.musicvenuetrust.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/MVT_2023-Annual-Report_Digital.pdf?fbclid=IwAR2rm8d7s65E4d0ZHqNgvAnFIuVAA_CttOf5yqRKFR9onVTJPNkkwoKI4vk">2023 年该行业状况的完整报告，</a>显示了<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/report-shows-disaster-facing-grassroots-music-venues-the-big-companies-and-arenas-are-now-going-to-have-to-answer-for-this-3576307">现场音乐面临的“灾难”，场馆以每周大约两个的速度关闭</a>。</p><p>该慈善机构<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-case-has-been-made-for-a-1-ticket-levy-on-all-arena-gigs-for-the-survival-of-grassroots-venues-and-artists-3611533">在威斯敏斯特展示了他们的调查结果</a>，并呼应了他们的呼吁，即<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-uks-new-arenas-respond-to-demand-to-invest-in-grassroots-music-venues-3391161">对竞技场规模及以上的演出门票征收 1 英镑的税，</a>并要求主要唱片公司向草根舞台回报，并认为“大公司现在将不得不对此作出回答”。</p><p>去年， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/legendary-music-venue-moles-in-bath-closes-after-45-years-today-is-a-very-sad-day-3553756">在巴斯传奇音乐场所 Moles 关闭后</a>，MVT 首席执行官 Mark Davyd 告诉<em>NME</em> ， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/2023-was-worst-year-for-venue-closures-while-no-one-in-music-industry-seems-to-care-say-mvt-3562266">现场音乐行业“对赚钱感兴趣，但对生态系统不感兴趣”。</a></p><p>其他新闻方面，本月早些时候，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/coldplay">酷玩乐队</a>宣布， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/coldplay-uk-tour-stadium-london-wembley-hull-music-venue-trust-tickets-3794308">即将在伦敦和赫尔举行的体育场演出的收益的 10% 将捐赠给音乐场馆信托基金</a>，以帮助支持全国各地的草根场馆。消息传出后， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/coldplay-fans-react-to-music-venue-trust-pledge-with-2025-uk-stadium-dates-this-is-the-start-of-something-big-3794446">粉丝们在社交媒体上做出了积极反应，有人说“这是大事的开始”</a> 。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/culture-secretary-lisa-nandy-condemns-oasis-dynamic-pricing-in-first-address-to-uk-music-industry-3802194">文化大臣丽莎·南迪 (Lisa Nandy) 在英国音乐产业的首次演讲中谴责 Oasis 的动态定价，</a>该演讲首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
